                            <comment id="14309951" author="stack" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 21:27:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for 0.98.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logs (every minute) if we come across a negative index. Outputs the inputs used in the modulo so we can get better understanding.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14309957" author="lhofhansl" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 21:31:31 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+              idx = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.abs(idx);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whoa, that can make things much worse, no?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14310062" author="enis" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 22:32:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could this be &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11200&quot; title=&quot;AsyncWriter of FSHLog might throw ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11200&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11200&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ? We have seen this in action using earlier 0.98 versions. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14310096" author="busbey" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 22:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+              idx = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.abs(idx);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whoa, that can make things much worse, no?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At this point idx should be in the range (-asyncSyncers.length, asyncSyncers.length) so taking the absolute value should be okay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Usually I&apos;d do a &amp;lt; 0 check and add the devisor, but I don&apos;t think it makes a difference unless this is a very hot code path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14310116" author="stack" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 23:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; I think you are right.  I was looking at wrong 0.98 version.  This is a patched 0.98.1 (CDH5.1.3).  It doesn&apos;t have &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11200&quot; title=&quot;AsyncWriter of FSHLog might throw ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11200&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11200&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Let me close this as a duplicate (Thanks for reviews &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; agree w/ Sean).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
